      "method_name": "Relative Frequency of Population Estimates (RFPE) Mapping",
      "description": "The primary method for generating spatiotemporal maps of relative population intensity based on calibrated cultural radiocarbon dates, incorporating temporal smoothing, kernel density estimation, and correction for sampling bias.",
      "steps": [
        {
          "step_number": 1,
          "category": "data_processing",
          "description": "Create a grid of points every 0.1° between 23-85°N and 173-51°W to define the area of interest (North America).",
          "searchable_summary": "create spatial grid for analysis area",
